      "content": "Cutting your dose in half without a proper blood test is a dangerous gamble, not a safe stabilization tactic. Your body needs precise levels, and suddenly dropping the dose can destabilize your mood, which is far worse than temporary nausea. For persistent symptoms, a quick call to your doctor's office is the most efficient route; they can often advise on minor adjustments over the phone to avoid unnecessary ER visits.",
